Description: Percentage of people who wore a mask most or all of the time while in public in the past 5 days
Definition (US): (C14 == 'most of the time' | C14 == 'all of the time') / any C14 response

Description: Percentage of people who wore a mask most or all of the time while in public in the past 7 days
Definition (US): (C14a == 'most of the time' | C14a == 'all of the time') / any C14a response
Definition (global): (C5 == 'most of the time' | C5 == 'all of the time') / any C5 response

Description: Percentage with COVID-like illness
Definition (US): B2 == 'fever' & (B2 == 'cough' | B2 == 'shortness of breath' | B2 == 'difficulty breathing' / any response to B2
Definition (global): B1 == 'fever' AND (B1 == 'cough' | B1 == 'shortness of breath' | B1 == 'difficulty breathing' / any response to B1

Description: Percentage with influenza-like illness
Definition (US): B2 == 'fever' & (B2 == 'cough' | B2 == 'sore throat') / any response to B2
Definition (global): B1 == 'fever' & (B1 == 'cough' | B1 == 'sore throat') / any response to B1

Description: Percentage of people reporting illness in their local community including their household
Definition (US): https://cmu-delphi.github.io/delphi-epidata/api/covidcast-signals/fb-survey.html#estimating-community-cli

Description: Percentage of respondents that have reported having had direct contact with people not staying with them.
Definition (US):
respondent = someone who answered any of the four contact types

# (responses to at least one contact type > 0) / # (responses to at least one contact type)
Definition (global): C1_m == 'yes' / any response to C1_m

Description: Percentage of respondents experiencing anosmia
Definition (US): B2 == 'loss of taste or smell' / any response to B2
Definition (global): B1_10 == 'yes' / any response to B1

Description: Percentage vaccinated
Definition (US): V1 == 'yes' / any response to V1
Definition (global): V1 == 'yes' / any response to V1

Description: Percentage receiving two doses
Definition (US): V2 == '2 doses' / any response to V2
Definition (global): V2 == '2 doses' / any response to V2

Description: Percentage who would definitely or probably choose to get vaccinated
Definition (US): (V3 == 'yes, definitely' | V3 == 'yes, probably') / any response to V3
Definition (global): (V3 == 'yes, definitely' | V3 == 'yes, probably') / any response to V3

Description: Percentage who would definitely or probably NOT choose to get vaccinated
Definition (US): (V3 == 'no, definitely not' | V3 == 'no, probably not') / any response to V3
Definition (global): (V3 == 'no, definitely not' | V3 == 'no, probably not') / any response to V3

Description: Percentage who have either already received a COVID vaccine or would definitely or probably choose to get vaccinated, if a vaccine were offered to them today.
Definition (US): (V1 == ‘yes’ | (V3 == ‘yes, definitely’ | V3 == ‘yes, probably’)) / (any response to V3 | (V1 == 'yes'))
Definition (global): (V1 == ‘yes’ | (V3 == ‘yes, definitely’ | V3 == ‘yes, probably’)) / (any response to V3 | (V1 == 'yes'))

Description: Percentage who would definitely choose to get vaccinated
Definition (US): V3|V3a == 'yes, definitely would' / any response to V3|V3a
Definition (global): V3|V3a == 'yes, definitely would' / any response to V3|V3a

Description: Percentage who would probably choose to get vaccinated
